  "title": "Nood Food Attendant",
  "description": "<p><strong>JOIN OUR FITNESS COMMUNITY AS ASMOOTHIE BAR SERVICE ATTENDANT!</strong></p><p>At Pure Group, we believe our people are our greatest strength. We're onthe lookout for energetic, positive, and service-oriented individuals to joinour team as <strong>Smoothie Bar Service Attendants</strong>. If you thrive in afast-paced, health-conscious environment and love engaging with people, this isyour chance to be part of a vibrant team that fuels our fitness community everyday.</p><p><strong>What You’ll Do:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Be the face of the brand:</strong> Greet members warmly and provide     a friendly, professional service experience</li><li><strong>Craft healthy goodness:</strong> Prepare and serve nutritious     smoothies, juices, coffee, and grab-and-go items for pre- and post-workout     nutrition</li><li><strong>Keep it fresh:</strong> Ensure the Grab-&-Go display     is consistently stocked, clean, and visually appealing</li><li><strong>Support the front desk:</strong> Assist with member inquiries and     provide support at the bar and reception when needed</li><li><strong>Maintain high standards:</strong> Uphold strict hygiene, food     safety, and cleanliness standards across the bar and prep areas</li><li><strong>Team collaboration:</strong> Work closely with the F&B     Supervisor and teammates, supporting additional duties as required</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Who We’re Looking For:</strong></p><ul><li>Friendly, outgoing personality\n     with a can-do attitude</li><li>Strong communication and\n     interpersonal skills</li><li>Reliable, punctual, and eager to\n     learn</li><li>Experience in F&B,\n     hospitality, or customer service is a plus—but not required!</li></ul>",
